el_questionnaire.1.player.reasons_belief: The best rational choice according to their interest and if I was that person.

el_questionnaire.1.player.comments_uncle: instruction are clear. the only thing in question is that how rational / trustworthy / greedy is the other partner, that would also determine my payoff (that is the one measured by stage 2). But if I were the leader, I have already tried to make the best decision for all.
el_questionnaire.1.player.reasons_effort: expected return for the leaders.  although the expected return for members is higher for X than Y, they basically have to do nothing to get it, and the risk borne by leader is greater due to the investment cost.    Given member will get return anyway (in most cases), while leaders risk is greater, so choose Y, of which expected return is greater
el_questionnaire.1.player.reasons_belief: not sure if I do well here, i chose 50:50 since the investment option may vary from person to person depending on characteristic, rationality level and risk aversion - i think
